link: Urgent Need! Sr. Data Analyst (Reporting Analyst)
job_title: Urgent Need! Sr. Data Analyst (Reporting Analyst)
job_description:
Kelly Services is seeking a Sr. Business Reporting Analyst for a leading insurance company located in Rapid City, SD.

Job Title: Business Reporting Analyst/ Sr. Data Analyst
Pay rate: $38 per hour (Rate is negotiable but will be based on resume and experience)

Location: Rapid City, SD, 57701


 Type: Contract
Length: 12 months (Likely go longer)
Job Purpose
The Senior Business Reporting Analyst is a key player in the Global Preneed Reporting team and broader Preneed organization with responsibility for leading efforts to automate and standardize reporting, writing advanced SQL queries and developing valuable analytical tools for the business. The Senior Analyst will work collaboratively with individuals across the organization, as well provide direct coaching and support to Reporting Analyst I and II’s. The position brings a working knowledge of the organization’s systems, expertise in the business areas as well as in current technology advances and capabilities. The Senior Business Reporting Analyst plays an active role in transforming the future of our organizations use of data and insightful reporting.
Basic Qualifications
Bachelor's degree in Computer/Management Information Systems or related field
5 years reporting experience.
Proficiency with MS Office (Word, Excel, Access and PowerPoint.)
Proficiency with data and reporting tools (SQL Services, VBA, Oracle, Power BI, SharePoint, etc.)
Education
Bachelor's degree in Computer/Management Information Systems or related field
8 years reporting experience.
Knowledge and Skills
Advanced level proficiency with MS Excel, including Power Query, Power Pivot, Power View, VBA.
Advanced SQL relational database knowledge including database design, structures, query writing, table set up and maintenance.
Advanced level proficiency with Microsoft SQL Server Reporting Services, including Report Builder and Visual Studio.
Prior experience working in Data or Reporting role in Life Insurance industry is a plus.
Experience coaching, collaborating and delegating in leadership capacity is desired
Strong communication skills (written and verbal)
Results oriented and self-motivated
Ability to analyze data and draw conclusions, provide recommendations
Ability to think critically and independently problem-solve
Ability to think innovatively
Ability to prioritize and manage multiple tasks and assignments in fast-paced, deadline-oriented environment
Ability to work collaboratively with teams across the organization
Ability to maintain confidentiality and act with a high degree of integrity

Important information:
This position is recruited for by a remote Kelly office, not your local Kelly branch. Please submit your resume to be considered for this position.
If this position may be interested to you, please email me back at somp767@kellyservices.com (with your most up to date resume in word format) and advise the best time and number at which you can be reached.

link: Sr. Sales Data Analyst-Complex Care Solutions
job_title: Sr. Sales Data Analyst-Complex Care Solutions
job_description:
Description:

For almost 30 years, Paradigm has been the industry leader in solving complex health care challenges and improving lives. With the most connected and experienced team in health care, we define and deliver outcomes that exceed financial and health expectations for our clients, as well as for individuals and their families.



Paradigm delivers its solutions through three divisions: Catastrophic Care Management, Complex Care Solutions and Specialty Networks. The Paradigm divisions are built on expertise from five best-in-class businesses: Paradigm Outcomes, The ALARIS Group, Encore Unlimited, ForeSight Medical and Adva-Net. Founded in 1991, Paradigm is headquartered in Walnut Creek, California with offices across the U.S. For more information, please visit https://www.paradigmcorp.com.



We are seeking a Sr. Sales Data Analyst to work in our Sioux Falls, SD location. The Senior Sales Data Analyst leads our sales team efforts to reach organic growth targets through data analysis. This role analyzes data, performs critical research, and develops and coordinates projects and communications to be implemented throughout the sales department.




Drive planning, analysis, coordination and consolidation of sales information and annual sales budgets with key business partners.
Work collaboratively with sales leaders, representatives and account managers to guide resource spend through data analytics.
Drive coordination, consolidation and review of the weekly and monthly sales results and help produce forecasts.
Create and maintain dashboards that tie back to business and product goals.
Develop a proficiency in and a business understanding of all of Paradigm CCS’s sales data sources.
Conduct ad hoc analysis using various financial analysis techniques, concepts and models to provide insightful comments and recommendations.
Identify untapped market potential, and develop recommendations to capture it.
Continually drive enhancement of financial models used to budget/forecast during monthly/quarterly/annual forecasting cycles.
Data visualization.
Support the executive team in a variety of projects and data needs.CCS19.

Requirements:


Bachelor’s degree in finance, economics, mathematics or similar quantitative discipline.
5+ years of experience in Corporate Finance, Sales Finance or Operations Finance.
Experience with large data sets and sophisticated models, proven proficiency with Excel, PowerPoint presentations and deck creation. Ability to learn specialized software.
Power BI exposure and proficiency with statistics software is a plus.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Ability to articulate business value of systems enhancements or process change. Able to communicate technical information to a non-technical audience.
Proven ability to analyze data and communicate findings to key stakeholders in a clear and concise format.
Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.
Entrepreneurial spirit to continue innovating and adding value; proactive communication style with the ability to build/foster relationships with business partners.
Strong work ethic and self-starter; can-do attitude and a high sense of urgency; ability to learn and deliver results in tight timeline.
Strong interpersonal skills. Able to work effectively with people and in teams.
Ability to adapt quickly to a changing environment.
